column6: be -> Name,/p/, /b/ -> Phoneme(s),bat -> English,approximation,/b/ in the combinations ⟨bb⟩ and ⟨bm⟩. -> Notes,
ez -> Name,/t͡s/, /d͡z/ -> Phoneme(s),rods -> English,approximation,/d͡z/ in the combination ⟨zz⟩. -> Notes,
áŋ -> Name,/ŋ/ -> Phoneme(s),sing -> English,approximation,/ɲ/ in Western Finnmark, except before a velar stop. -> Notes,
pe -> Name,/p/, /hp/, /pʰ/ -> Phoneme(s),park -> English,approximation,/hp/ after a voiced consonant. /pʰ/ at the beginning of a stressed syllable. -> Notes,
á -> Name,/aː/, /a/ -> Phoneme(s),chai -> English,approximation,In Eastern Finnmark, also /æ/ or /æː/. -> Notes,
ež -> Name,/t͡ʃ/, /d͡ʒ/ -> Phoneme(s),hedge -> English,approximation,/d͡ʒ/ in the combination ⟨žž⟩. -> Notes,
če -> Name,/tʃ/, /htʃ/ -> Phoneme(s),chew -> English,approximation,/htʃ/ after a voiced consonant. -> Notes,
ce -> Name,/ts/, /hts/ -> Phoneme(s),lets -> English,approximation,/hts/ after a voiced consonant. -> Notes,
ko -> Name,/k/, /hk/, /kʰ/ -> Phoneme(s),cat -> English,approximation,/hk/ after a voiced consonant. /kʰ/ at the beginning of a stressed syllable. -> Notes,
i -> Name,/i/, /iː/, /j/ -> Phoneme(s),me -> English,approximation,/j/ after a vowel. -> Notes,

te -> Name,/t/, /ht/, /tʰ/, /h(t)/, /θ/ -> Phoneme(s),told -> English,approximation,/ht/ after a voiced consonant. /tʰ/ at the beginning of a stressed syllable. /h(t)/ word-finally. /θ/ in the combination tk. -> Notes,
de -> Name,/t/, /d/, /ð/ -> Phoneme(s),do -> English,approximation,/d/ in the combinations ⟨dd⟩, ⟨dn⟩ and ⟨dnj⟩. /ð/ between two unstressed vowels. -> Notes,
ge -> Name,/k/, /ɡ/ -> Phoneme(s),go -> English,approximation,/ɡ/ in the combinations ⟨gg⟩ and ⟨gŋ⟩. In Western Finnmark, /d/ in ⟨gŋ⟩ instead. -> Notes,
a -> Name,/a/ -> Phoneme(s),spa -> English,approximation,Also /aː/ in Western Finnmark. In Eastern Finnmark, /ɑ/ or /ɑː/ in stressed syllables, /a/ or /aː/ in unstressed syllables. -> Notes,
